When programming an unbalanced binary search tree, you discover that your search time is still linear. Which of the following best explains why your search time is linear?

choices.W: Values are not being added such that they follow the binary search tree inequality
choices.X: Values are added in a strictly increasing or decreasing order.
choices.Z: The search algorithm is using breadth first search

answer: X) VALUES ARE ADDED IN A STRICTLY INCREASING OR DECREASING ORDER.

Which of the following best describes a minimum spanning tree?

choices.W: A tree that only covers a proper subset of the vertices in a graph
choices.X: A tree formed from the contraction of edges between vertices of high degree
